<br>
We had the most success once the Lords conned blue to us. Then we would resist the charms about 75% of the time. Remember to keep shielding on, that raises magic resistance.<br>
<br>
Once Lord Soptyver shows up, you're done. You can't pull eyes single when he's there, and he's too big for you to deal with at your level. <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 33rd Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uaramondthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AramondTheMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(12/10/01 12:55:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Evil Eyes...</span><hr size=1> HI There!<br>
<br>
I am a lvl 19 Mage now and fought in Beholder solo and later in a group of two!<br>
Absolutely cool place when you want your small brick of ore used for researching you Earthi. Besides you can make good money with the muddite elders and the chasm minos. But the elders are middle blue with 19 and the chasm minos white to yellow with 19. (all yellow with 1<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
The good thing on the eyes is the loot. They usually drop stuff for about 4-5 pp. Not that bad for lvl19 I think. But the main advantage of beholders is when you want to raise your trade skills. I hunt there mainly for the ore. I need it to make the studs used in tailoring. By the way you can raise your tailoring in EK by killing carrions and Crags very fast. Did so to get rid of my low lvl looted Armor. <br>
<br>
An advice last...<br>
Don't ever attack the eye solo. You'll get kicked ass. With my druid friend 22 it's very easy to nuke it out fast. I never tried it solo because with lvl 16 when it was yellow for me a friend of mine and me (he ench) attacked it. Shouldn't have been a problem with two pets and 2 nukers. He died... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.showPrevMessage?topicID=6.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.showNextMessage?topicID=6.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.threadControl?topicID=6.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm41.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45"